The CSS should not be in one style.css file for the whole application:

Separate CSS per each component, in their respective folder or area please add <module-name>.module.css.
Then in SolidJS the module is imported and used as shown below.

Example Checkbox.tsx component:

```ts
import ui from './Checkbox.module.css'

type CheckboxProps = {
  checked: boolean
  onChange: (checked: boolean, ev: Event) => void
}

export function Checkbox(props: CheckboxProps) {
  return (
    <input
      type="checkbox"
      classList={{ [ui.checkbox as string]: true }}
      checked={props.checked}
      onChange={(ev) => {
        props.onChange(ev.target.checked, ev)
      }}
    />
  )
}

```

Example CSS file:

```css
.checkbox {
  --color: var(--neutral-500);
  --color-hover: black;
  --border-color: var(--neutral-500);
  --border-color-hover: black;
  --check-color: white;

  [data-theme='dark'] & {
    --color: var(--neutral-400);
    --color-hover: white;
    --border-color: var(--neutral-700);
    --border-color-hover: var(--neutral-500);
    --check-color: black;
  }
}

.checkbox {
  appearance: none;
  outline: none;
  margin: 0;
  width: 1.2em;
  height: 1.2em;
  border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
  border-radius: var(--space-1);
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  cursor: pointer;

  &:hover:not(:disabled) {
    --color: var(--color-hover);
    --border-color: var(--border-color-hover);
  }

  &::before {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    width: 1em;
    height: 1em;
    opacity: 0;
    background-color: var(--color);
    /* manually drawn and fine tuned */
    mask-image: url('data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 11 11"><path d="M 2.5 5.5 L 4.5 7.5 L 8.5 3" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>');
  }

  &:checked {
    border: none;
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom,
      var(--color),
      oklab(from var(--color) calc(l * 0.8) a b)
    );
    background-size: cover;

    &::before {
      opacity: 1;
      background-color: var(--check-color);
    }
  }
}

```

Find how this generally works with this CSS modules and if any NPM deps are needed, and set this up.

Then use this approach for all features/components that we currently have in the frontend SolidJS application.
The App.module.css for the main Application component can ofc be a bit bigger and contain shared and App related CSS.
Organize as see fit, but with above rules (one CSS file per CSS module, used in that component, or shared between multiple components if it makes sense)

